description:
Hisoka is tired of playing sidekick to his ditzy partner Tsuzuki, and wants some power of his own. He decides to travel into the imaginary realm in search of magical shiki spirit allies. Tzusuki tags along as a guide, but gets called back on an assignment before Hisoka has made his selection. Alone at last, Hisoka finds himself in a world of trouble. Now it's up to Tsuzuki to rescue him...uh-oh!

Chapter 28 - 36.

description:
Plot Summary

When Jin Kazama declares the powerful Mishima Zaibatsu an independent nation and claims 200 strategic economic zones around the world as his territory, he soon finds himself at war with forty separate nations. Jin's cousin Asuka is a high school student who likes to break up fights wherever she finds them, and as Jin is family, she sees it as a personal responsibility to put an end to the conflict he has began by bringing him in.

Following her first dubious attempt to apprehend Jin, Asuka returns to her home in Osaka where she must fend off an obnoxious foreigner.

Chapter Titles

  • Battle 1: Legend of the Phoenix
  • Battle 2: Girl Bomb
  • Battle 3: Wild Flower
  • Battle 4: Dusk's Paper Airplane
  • Battle 5: Reason
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Kitty Bo Bitty in The Big City

description:
Jonathan Fierce, a profiler for the FBI gifted with psychic abilities, failed to stop an explosion which has just killed his team of fellow agents, the only real family he's ever had. The FBI wants to charge him with the crime. Now he's being hunted by the Feds and is on the run from the crime syndicate that killed his team. Miraculously, Fierce can hear the voices of his slain teammates, giving him the skills and abilities to become a one-man strike force. Now he's going deep under cover into the Jamaican underworld to strike at the heart of the syndicate and uncover the facts behind the conspiracy against him. Collecting the four-issue series.

Jeremy and Robert Love, the creative force behind Gettosake Entertainment and the masterminds who brought comics fans Midnight Mover, now bring you the slickest, most stylish and suspenseful action thriller on stands today.
name: TPB

description: This volume collects all four of the action packed G.I. Joe Yearbooks. Re-caps of important story lines, character profiles, and new stories were presented in these yearly comics that were published from 1985-1988. It also includes cover galleries and pin-ups by G.I. JOE cover artist Mike Zeck.
name: TPB

description: Clayface has a cunning plan: he's going to Gotham's Comic Con, where he can blend in! Fans, artists and cosplayers form a big, bold backdrop to Batman and Robin's effort to track him down, and along the way, they learn a little about what heroes mean to those who admire them.
name: Gotham Comiccon!

description: The Wollebollen are environmentally friendly creatures that keep the forrests clean. But they are abused by a witch who forces them to rob banks. Luckily Marcel Kiekeboe is nearby...
name: De Wollebollen

description: Near the Bermuda Islands, Thimotheus Triangl has discovered the sunken city of Attallattanta and her golden treasures. He wants to become world's mightiest man, thanks to the discovery. He makes airplanes and boats disappear. But then Kiekeboe, Fanny en Konstantinopel end up in Attallattanta...
name: De Duivelse Driehoek

description: Bibi Pralin Gaga is the dictator of the African republic Boeloe Boeloe. Because Charlotte suddenly develops an unbelievable admiration for the dictator, the family Kiekeboe gets invited by the president himself. In Boeloe Boeloe they discover that some things are not right...
name: De Dorpstiran Van Boeloe Boeloe

description: Konstantinopel gets beamed by the head of the statue of a sphinx. To undo the paralyzing effect and learn the secret of the sphinx, Kiekeboe travels, in the company of archeologist Vladimir Zarkovaag, to Egypt. A mysterious green mummy and his assistent Balthazar are on his heels.
name: De Onthoofde Sfinx

description: Marcel Kiekeboe becomes approver for the appleblueseagreen restaurant guide. Soon he notices a swindle with the appointed stars. Not only the demonic Orgieter, but also Fanny's new friend Carrot, a vegetarian, is involved in the affair.
name: Tegen De Sterren Op

description: The family Kiekeboe attend a performance of the comic Herman Gaaikevliet in Carr (Amsterdam). Before, during and after the performance strange things happen that lead to hunt for a painting of the spy Mata Hari.
name: Kiekeboe In Carr

description: Hisoka won't leave the Imaginary World until he has some Shiki spirits of his own. But strange "wormholes" keep ripping open the sky, threatening the end of the Imaginary World--and one sucks Hisoka right into the realm of the fearsome dragon Kurikara! How can Tsuzuki save his partner from the powerful Shiki he once failed to tame? And why are the other Shinigami investigating Hisoka's family back on Earth?
name: Vol. 10

description: Guest starring Bloodwulf! As a darkness hangs over the city, the Red Dragon's plans are finally revealed. Avengelyne Father Peter, Passover, and Heaven are transported to Hell, where they must fight their way out of its seven levels and find the unlikeliest of help. Plus, a Graveyard Shift back-up story by MARK POULTON and JON MALIN (YOUNGBLOOD) and Barker by OWEN GIENI.
name: In the Mouth of Madness, Part One

John Byrne's Next Men gets re-colored and re-packaged! Starting with the prequel story 2112, strap yourself in for a wild ride as the members of Project Next Men are thrust into our world and left to their own (super-powered) devices.
name: Vol. 1

description: Classic Next Men Volume 2 follows the adventures of the Next Men as they come to grips with their unfathomable past, and the role they have yet to play in preventing the future demise of mankind! Including the M4 backup stories which later merge into the main storyline, Next Men is comic storytelling and illustration pulsing at its best.
name: Vol. 2

description:
June is getting steamy!

Alexia and Madame LeFoux are bringing the heat to this months cover of YEN PLUS, and its only getting hotter inside! The kids from the flock have found a way to cool down as they head for the Antarctic, but somehow trouble seems to find those kids no matter where they go Nick is weathering the humidity down in New Orleans, but with a killer out for his head, things are probably gonna get a lot worse before they get better. And speaking of getting better, it seems like Lord Maccon has finally emerged from his formaldehyde-fueled bender. Maybe he can even find a way to make amends with the lovely Alexia

Weve got all of this, chapter 24 of SOUL EATER NOT! and much, much more inside this months issue. Not a bad way to kick off a long, hot summer at all!

Contains chapters from the following manga:

  • Soulless - Chapter 19
  • Maximum Ride - Chapter 55
  • Milkyway Hitchhiking - Chapter 22
  • Miss Peregrine's Home For Peculiar Children - Chapter 4
  • The Dark-Hunters: Infinity - Chapter 10
  • Aron's Absurd Armada - Chapter 35
  • Jack Frost - Chapter 62
  • Soul Eater NOT! - Chapter 24

The Infernal Devices returns to YEN PLUS, kicking off with the first installment of Clockwork Princess! We last left off with a marriage proposal, an untimely love confession, and the unexpected arrival of a certain little sisteryou definitely wont want to miss what new surprises await the Infernal cast!

But thats not all! As Jacob gets to spend more time with the peculiar kids in Miss Peregrine, hes finding more reasons to stay in the past than return to the present, especially with mysterious occurrences and a new stranger in town. A reunion may be in the works between Lord Maccon and Alexia in Soulless, but something more sinister may be waiting for Max and the flock beyond the South Poles snow white mountains in Maximum Ride And who knows sinister better than Nick Gautier who, aside from having recurring visions of his own death, still needs to survive high school in Dark-Hunters!

While the girls are on a break in Soul Eater NOT! this month, theres still so much more inside this months issue (you wont believe it!) that if you havent subscribed yet (we cant believe it!), youll definitely want to!

description:
Iddar the mysterious shaman of the great plains calls for a tribal meeting as a sacred bird; a Turul is captured. Will there be truce or bloodshed before the meeting is adjourned?

Also the young nameless one debuts in this issue!

Iddar and his nameless companion are trapped in an ancient cave - the Valgabs Gorge a trap that was set up by Iddar himself? As evil plans being hatched in a far-away village, the nameless one earns a name!

Emese, along with her new-born child and nurse, are lost in forest with a pack of wolves hot on their trail. Only Iddar and his young archer companion could save them from certain doom. But do they want to be rescued at all? Also, the Caravan storyline starts here

When Jonny Zero's blood was infused with lifesaving nanotech plasm his life was changed forever. No longer simply a teenaged boy, Jonny became GO BOY 7 Human Action Machine! Now Jonny's life is one adventure after another as he battles the evil, nonsensical genius of THE CULTIST who seeks the destruction of logic, reason, and Go Boy 7! In this collection, the Cultist's devastating creativity with anarchic giga-technology threatens civilization yet again, and an enigmatic new player is in town: BioAgent! Who is this sudden hero, what is happening to Jonny's body, and what is the origin of the Cultist? Collecting issues #5-#8 of the series.

Dont miss out on this second collection of ROCKET COMICS' foremost title, featuring the storytelling talents of Brian Augustyn (B.P.R.D.: Dark Waters, Crimson, The Flash, JLA: Year One) and the kinetic art of hot young newcomers Jon Sommariva and Todd Demong!
name: Volume 2

description:
Haloone of the largest video games franchisescomes to Dark Horse!

Before she was a super solider defending humanity as part of the Spartan IV program, Sarah Palmer was an ODSTOrbital Drop Shock Troopercarrying out the most dangerous missions behind enemy lines!

This is a seven-page digital preview of Halo: Initiation #1.

  • A new era of Halo comics begins at Dark Horse!
  • The origin of Sarah Palmerand the Spartan IV program!
  • The Halo franchise has sales eclipsing $3 billion over its lifetime.
  • From one of the writers on Halo 4comics veteran Brian Reed!

A MAN WITH NO PAST HAS SIX DAYS TO RECOVER HIS FUTURE. Dan Hutton lost everything. Adrift in the witness relocation program, Dan is told his new identity has been compromised - by two different groups each claiming to be US agents. Not knowing who to trust, Dan runs - back to the world that took everything he loved.

Back Blurb

Dan Hutton lost everything... his name, his past, his life, his wife.

Adrift and forgotten in a witness relocation program, Dan is told that his new identity has been compromised... by two different groups each claiming to be US agents. Not knowing who he can or should trust, Dan runs -- back to the world that took everything he loved from him.

Now, a man with no past has six days to recover his future.

The classic noir thriller of repressed memory, shadow agents, forced perception and lost love by Steven T. Seagle (it's a bird..., The Red Diary/The RE[a]D Diary, Genius) and Stefano Gaudiano (Daredevil, Harbinger, Winter Soldier) is presented in "full" color for the first time.
name: HC
